text.tspan: Global meat demand if everyone ate like the average citizen of...,
Hypothetical global meat demand if everyone in the world ate the same quantity as the average citizen of a given country, e.g. data
for the USA in 1990 hypothesises global meat demand if everyone in the world consumed the same amount of meat as the average
US citizen in 1990. Actual global meat production in 2013 was 310 million tonnes.
Data source: Our World in Data based on the Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations
